Description: Fragment of a calcite Dynasty 26 canopic jar later reused as an ostracon to draw a figure in Hellenistic style. Scholars have interpreted the figure to be an angel or saint based on the function of the site as a monastery in Late Antiquity.
Bibliographic references: Naville 1907-1913 / The XIth Dynasty Temple at Deir el-Bahari (3:21 and pl. 34, no.9)
